  "prompt": "What social media platforms are best to use for a restaurant and how often should someone post?",
  "response": "For restaurants, the best social media platforms are:\n\n1. Instagram (most effective)\n- Visual platform perfect for food photos\n- Use Stories and Reels\n- Recommended posting: 3-5 times per week\n- Showcase dishes, behind-the-scenes, specials\n\n2. Facebook\n- Good for events, promotions, and customer engagement\n- Share menu updates, hours, specials\n- Recommended posting: 2-3 times per week\n- Helpful for older demographic\n\n3. TikTok\n- Growing platform for food content\n- Short, entertaining videos\n- Recommended posting: 2-3 times per week\n- Great for reaching younger audience\n\n4. Twitter\n- Quick updates, promotions, customer interaction\n- Recommended posting: 1-2 times per day\n- Good for real-time communication\n\n5. Pinterest\n- Share recipes, food photography\n- Recommended posting: 1-2 times per week\n- More niche, but good for recipe-focused content\n\nGeneral posting tips:\n- Maintain consistent branding\n- Use high-quality images\n- Engage with followers\n- Use relevant hashtags\n- Mix content types (food, staff, events)\n- Post during peak dining hours\n\nFrequency can vary, but consistency is key.",
